The paper deals with logo detection and retrieval using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of CNNs for logo detection and comparison also suggests the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The proposed open set approach involves training task-specific CNNs, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
